label.value: decreased cellular 5-phosphoribosyl diphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 5-phosphoribosyl diphosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular hercynylcysteine sulfoxide level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of hercynylcysteine sulfoxide measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular CDP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of CDP measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular UMP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of UMP measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular adenine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of adenine measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular UDP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of UDP measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular sedoheptulose-7-phosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of sedoheptulose-7-phosphate measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular pentose phosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more pentose phosphates measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: abolished calcium-transporting ATPase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a calcium-transporting ATPase activity is absent.

label.value: decreased calcium ion transport from cytosol to endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of calcium ions from the cytosol to the endoplasmic reticulum is decreased.

label.value: abolished protein phosphorylation during glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: abolished protein phosphorylation during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur during a cellular response to salt stress.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to alkaline pH

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal during a cellular response to a pH above 7.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein phosphorylation during cellular response to alkaline pH

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur during a cellular response to a pH above 7.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cellular acetyl-CoA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of acetyl-CoA measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased cellular malonyl-CoA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of malonyl-CoA measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular free fatty acid level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more free fatty acids measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: large and small daughter nuclei

value.value: A mitosis phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the nucleus divides unequally to produce one daughter nucleus that is larger than the other.

definition.value: This phenotype does not necessarily reflect a chromosome segregation defect. It may instead arise from abnormal nuclear envelope assembly, following normal chromosome segregation.

label.value: large and small daughter nuclei, with unequal nuclear envelope distribution

value.value: A mitosis phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromosomes segregate equally (i.e. normally), but the nuclear envelope is not distributed equally between daughter nuclei. As a result, the nucleus divides unequally to produce one daughter nucleus that is larger than the other.

label.value: normal growth on sodium chloride

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing sodium chloride, usually at a higher level than in standard media.

label.value: increased duration of protein phosphorylation during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of protein phosphorylation is longer than normal during a cellular response to osmotic stress. All phosphorylation may be affected, or only phosphorylation of specific proteins, or even specific sites within specific proteins.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished mitochondrial fission during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial fission does not occur during a cellular response to osmotic stress. Normally, mitochondria undergo fission when the cell is exposed to hyperosmotic conditions.

label.value: normal cell cycle regulation during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the regulation of the mitotic cell cycle in response to osmotic stress is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Normally, cell cycle progression is slowed or arrested transiently following exposure to osmotic stress.

label.value: abolished protein localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the Cdr2 medial cortical node complex does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the Cdr2 medial cortical node complex is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein exit from Cdr2 medial cortical node complex during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that normally moves away from Cdr2 medial cortical node complexes during a cellular response to osmotic stress instead remains predominantly in the nodes.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein exit from Cdr2 medial cortical node complex during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which movement of a protein away from Cdr2 medial cortical node complexes during a cellular response to osmotic stress is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal microtubule binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of microtubule binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The relevant gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with microtubules that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal CMG complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which CMG complex assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished mitotic DNA replication elongation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which DNA strand elongation involved in mitotic nuclear DNA replication does not occur.

label.value: abolished mitotic DNA replication initiation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the initiation of nuclear DNA replication does not occur at one or more origins.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin distal to replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to regions of chromatin distal to replication origins is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal mitotic DNA replication elongation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which strand elongation during nuclear DNA replication is abnormal.

label.value: decreased CMG complex progression from replication origin

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the CMG complex moves away from replication origins to a lesser extent than normal.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin distal to replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to transcribed regions of chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal CMG complex progression from replication origin

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which movement of the CMG complex away from replication origins during DNA replication is normal.

label.value: delayed onset of protein localization to chromatin at replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at replication origins begins later than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: resistance to tschimganine

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of tschimganine than normal.

label.value: stationary phase viability unaffected by tschimganine

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which the proportion of cells in the population remains viable after entering stationary phase does not change in the presence of tschimganine. Normally, wild-type cell populations survive longer in the presence of tschimganine than in its absence.

definition.value: Although each cell has a replicative lifespan in that it divides a certain number of times and then dies, replicative lifespan is often measured at the population level, where it is defined by the number of generations at which 50% of the starting cells are dead.

label.value: stationary phase viability unaffected by alpha-hibitakanine

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which the proportion of cells in the population remains viable after entering stationary phase does not change in the presence of alpha-hibitakanine. Normally, wild-type cell populations survive longer in the presence of alpha-hibitakanine than in its absence.

definition.value: Although each cell has a replicative lifespan in that it divides a certain number of times and then dies, replicative lifespan is often measured at the population level, where it is defined by the number of generations at which 50% of the starting cells are dead.

label.value: stationary phase viability unaffected by beta-hibitakanine

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which the proportion of cells in the population remains viable after entering stationary phase does not change in the presence of beta-hibitakanine. Normally, wild-type cell populations survive longer in the presence of beta-hibitakanine than in its absence.

definition.value: Although each cell has a replicative lifespan in that it divides a certain number of times and then dies, replicative lifespan is often measured at the population level, where it is defined by the number of generations at which 50% of the starting cells are dead.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at MCB promoters during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at promoters that contain MCB sites is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at MCB promoters during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at promoters that contain MCB sites is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased nucleosome occupancy at MCB promoters

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is greater than normal at promoters containing one or more MluI cell cycle box factor elements (MCBs). Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: normal transcription from MCB promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more MluI cell cycle box factor elements (MCBs) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in extent, timing, start or termination site, etc.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased during a cellular response to osmotic stress.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to tschimganine

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased during a cellular response to tschimganine.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal cell wall thickness during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the thickness of the cell wall is abnormal. The wall may be uniformly thicker or thinner than normal, or thickness may be irregular.

label.value: decreased cell wall thickness at cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the fungal-type cell wall is thinner than normal at one or both cell tips.

label.value: asymmetric mitochondrial aggregation at old end

value.value: An abnormal intracellular mitochondrion distribution phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondria cluster together more than normal, distal to the side of the nucleus near the old cell end.
